article.headline: Texas-Arlington 70, Texas-Permian Basin 47
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Marquez Haynes and Brandon Long each scored 19 points to lead Texas-Arlington to a 70-47 victory over Texas-Permian Basin on Tuesday night. Long scored 11 of his points in the first 20 minutes, and Haynes, who came into the game averaging 30.3 points, shot 6 of 11, including 5 of 7 from 3-point range. The Mavericks (2-2) led 38-24 at halftime and extended their lead to as much as 24 in the second half. Elijah Thomas had 11 points for the Falcons (0-2), who suited up only eight players. Two players were out due to injury and another was not with the team.
